post_text: We learned today that a student at the Great Plains Technology Center tested positive for Covid 19. The student is not from Tipton but Tipton students were in the same classroom. post_text: Packets for Tipton Elementary School students will be ready for pickup from 9:00 am-11:00 am on Monday, April 6th. Please pull up to the cafeteria door (just North of the office door) and the packet will be brought out to your vehicle. If your child has a library book at home, please return it at that time. We request that you stay in your vehicle to limit exposure. We miss our students dearly, but want to keep everyone safe and healthy. If this time frame does not work for you, please contact Amy Ferris at 580-471-7825, to schedule a more convenient time.

On behalf of the Lady Tigers Basketball Team I would like to say "THANK YOU" to all of our fans! Because of your financial help, we were able to provide for the girls at the regional tournament last week. We also deeply appreciate those who could make it to the games last week and all year. It didn’t end where and when we wanted, but because of our fans it was a great year. I know all the basketball teams really appreciate all that you do for us. Thanks again for a fantastic year!
Coach White.

Tipton fans:
Corn Bible called me last night after the game and informed us they were cancelling their season due to not having enough players. So, as of now, we do not have a game for next Friday night. We do not currently have a plan for Senior Night activities, but we will figure something out. We are looking for a team to play, but the odds of finding one at this point are slim. We will keep you informed.

post_text: Attention parents of JH and HS Boy/Girl athletes at Tipton Schools: We will NOT be taking a bus for free physicals this year. You will need to get a physical for your child. This can be done with their personal doctor, OR Dr. Mefford and Dr. Howard in Frederick are both doing sports physicals if you will call and make an appointment they will get you taken care of. There are copies of the physical form that you need to take with you to the appointment in the HS office, Admin office, or the MS office. If you have any questions or concerns please feel free to contact Coach White he will be glad to help you. Physicals have to be completed before your child can practice.

Tipton Tigers All Sports Booster Club
May 21, 2019 at 11:23 AM ·

We are excited that the Tipton Tigers are hosting their first ever football team camp in Tipton! Coach White has given us a list of his needs for this camp and we need your help!

Wednesday and Thursday, May 29/30 at noon, we will be feeding the teams. This will be approximately 200 people each day. We need to hamburger meat, buns, cheese, chili, chips, plates, napkins. We have hot dogs, ketchup, mustard, mayo and pickles. We will be taking monetary or food donations.

If you would like to help, please give monetary donations to Greg or Molly Lucas or Joe or Lori Waugh. If you would like to provide a certain food item, please comment below.

Greg Lucas will be cooking the hamburgers and hot dogs for the teams. We will let you know of other needs as the camp approaches. Thank you, Tipton Tiger fans!

shared_text:
North Fork News added 168 new photos to the album: STATE TOURNAMENT PICTURES — with Rreana Mcbride and 10 others at Tipton Public Schools.
March 1, 2019 at 5:46 PM · Tipton, OK ·

From the send-off to the last buzzer it was a day of excitement, fun and in the end...heartbreak. Tipton would lose to Frontier 63-61, but they have made themselves known to Class A girls basketball. Thanks to Coach Teddy White and Misti Tyler, the girl's basketball program is quickly gaining the hearts and passion of the community. Establishing a good girls program is not easy in a town that's all about football. But...it's happening! And it's wonderful! Packed stands, loud fans, and great girls basketball are here to stay. Who wasn't proud last night...even after the loss? This is just the beginning! Great things ahead! Go Lady Tigers!
